    {
      "id": "We9_u0tKvFwpfIOuHbwBa",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 280.30995178222656,
      "y": 1670,
      "width": 1282.63916015625,
      "height": 625,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aU",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 76627163,
      "version": 1282,
      "versionNonce": 390764629,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1780118442568,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- Langsmith and Langfuse (you can see traces of agents how it works for each request)\n\n- Grafana will show your trends across multiple request\n\n- Prometheus ( A time series database) -> 15s for every secodns it scrapes the data from app and store\n- Grafana here will be the dashboard UI  that renders beautiful charts, alerts from the prometheus data\n\n- what we track?- Token per minute, cost per hour,latency, agent wise latency,  sucess rate and rate rate (app and tool), user load\n- Alerts: Get notified on slack/email when cost exceeds the budget , latency issue, error &% increase\n- Open source tool can be run in docker and self hosted\n\n\n, \n\nKey Metrics:\n\nRequestRate[5s] - How many request has been received / processed in 5s - Time series chart- alert <0 \nP95 latency - 95% of the time what is the avg latency - Gauge cahrt - alert like if it excced > 10s\nError rate [5s] = How much of % of request gettin gfailed - KPI - if the error rate > 10%\nTokens/Hours - How much token been used every hours - chart - >500k/hr\nCost Estimate /hour - how much cost the app incured in an hour - chart - >$5/hr\nSession - How much session been active - >2session\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- Langsmith and Langfuse (you can see traces of agents how it works for each request)\n\n- Grafana will show your trends across multiple request\n\n- Prometheus ( A time series database) -> 15s for every secodns it scrapes the data from app and store\n- Grafana here will be the dashboard UI  that renders beautiful charts, alerts from the prometheus data\n\n- what we track?- Token per minute, cost per hour,latency, agent wise latency,  sucess rate and rate rate (app and tool), user load\n- Alerts: Get notified on slack/email when cost exceeds the budget , latency issue, error &% increase\n- Open source tool can be run in docker and self hosted\n\n\n, \n\nKey Metrics:\n\nRequestRate[5s] - How many request has been received / processed in 5s - Time series chart- alert <0 \nP95 latency - 95% of the time what is the avg latency - Gauge cahrt - alert like if it excced > 10s\nError rate [5s] = How much of % of request gettin gfailed - KPI - if the error rate > 10%\nTokens/Hours - How much token been used every hours - chart - >500k/hr\nCost Estimate /hour - how much cost the app incured in an hour - chart - >$5/hr\nSession - How much session been active - >2session\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
